    • Method Detail

      • published

        java.util.Optional<java.lang.Float> published()
        The published magnetic variation from source data. This is based on measurements that may have been taken historically or etc. Typically when available this is what is preferentially used in automated systems such as aircraft FMS's, etc.

      • modeled

        float modeled()
        The modeled value for variation typically based on the WMM (World Magnetic Model) published by NOAA and provided in Declinations.

      • magneticToTrue

        default java.lang.Double magneticToTrue(java.lang.Double course)
        Converts the input magnetic course to a true course using the published local variation if provided otherwise defaulting to the modeled value.

      • trueToMagnetic

        default java.lang.Double trueToMagnetic(java.lang.Double course)
        Converts the input true course to a magnetic course using the published local variation if provided otherwise defaulting to the modeled value.
